Package org.ivoa.dm.dataset.dataset

Class DataModel

java.lang.Object
org.ivoa.dm.dataset.dataset.DataModel
All Implemented Interfaces:
org.ivoa.vodml.jpa.JPAManipulations, org.ivoa.vodml.jpa.JPAManipulationsForObjectType<Long>
@Entity @VoDml(id="ds:dataset.DataModel", role=objectType) public class DataModel extends Object implements org.ivoa.vodml.jpa.JPAManipulationsForObjectType<Long>
This object provides specific information regarding the data model and version thereof that a dataset represents. This information is primarily an aide to (de)serialization of the dataset. As such, it would better be defined by serialization conventions. In lieu of such conventions, we include this object and representative serialization examples for the primary file formats VOTable and FITS. objectType: DataModel

    • name

      @VoDml(id="ds:dataset.DataModel.name", role=attribute, type="ivoa:string", typeRole=primitiveType) protected String name
      Formatted string providing the name and version of the model document. The format speficication is '[name]-[version].[subversion]'. Each derived model should specifically state the appropriate string for this field. : Attribute name : multiplicity 1

    • prefix

      @VoDml(id="ds:dataset.DataModel.prefix", role=attribute, type="ivoa:string", typeRole=primitiveType) protected String prefix
      Prefix string used in UType string for elements associated with the model. For IVOA standard models, this will be a predetermined string (e.g. 'stc' or 'spec'). Extended, or user defined content can specify a unique prefix for their own content. : Attribute prefix : multiplicity 0..1

    • URL

      @VoDml(id="ds:dataset.DataModel.URL", role=attribute, type="ivoa:anyURI", typeRole=primitiveType) protected String URL

      public DataModel(String name, String prefix, String URL)
      full parameter constructor.
      Parameters:
      name - Formatted string providing the name and version of the model document. The format speficication is '[name]-[version].[subversion]'. Each derived model should specifically state the appropriate string for this field.
      prefix - Prefix string used in UType string for elements associated with the model. For IVOA standard models, this will be a predetermined string (e.g. 'stc' or 'spec'). Extended, or user defined content can specify a unique prefix for their own content.
      URL - URL pointer to the XML schema associated with the model.
